main event: A sighting of an unidentified flying object near Champagne, Yukon, Canada on May 29, 1960.
interesting points: The object was approximately 50 ft. in diameter with two flat spots on the bottom.,The object was estimated to be at an altitude of 10,000 to 15,000 ft. high.,The object exhibited tumbling behavior as it was observed.,The observation lasted for about 2 to 3 minutes.,The report indicates a lack of additional information and photographs.
